column4: The document number assigned to a patent application on publication. e.g. 20130227762

A string used to identify a patent. Important to note: this is not always a consistent 'identifier' as such as a combination of jurisdiction, document number, application stage that can be used to identify a patent document. While most patent id formats can be used to uniquely id patents, different datasets might use different formats.
The DocDB identifier of a patent document (assigned by EPO worldwide bibliographic data)
Information pertaining to the patent's family
Date of publication, for a paper or patent document
Identifier associated with biomedical and life sciences journal literature
Unique lens identifier. Every document in the Lens has a unique 15-digit identifier called a Lens ID. e.g. 186-488-232-022-055
Digital Object Identifier, used to uniquely ID academic papers
